FBIS4-62719 "drsov095_a_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-095 Daily Report 17 May 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Grachev, Perry Discuss Joint Military Exercises Grachev, Perry Discuss Joint Military Exercises LD1705083594 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network in Russian 0500 GMT 17 May 94 LD1705083594 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network Russian BFN [From the "Novosti" newscast] [Text] Defense Minister Pavel Grachev and U.S. Defense Secretary William Perry discussed Russian-American exercises in a telephone conversation and agreed on a meeting in Brussels. Yelena Agapova, aide to the Russian minister, told INTERFAX that the telephone conversation took place on Monday [16 May] night at the request of the United States. Pavel Grachev supported the idea of holding joint Russian-American command and staff exercises at the Totskoye testing range but said that Russian legislators still had to make a final decision on this. During the conversation, Grachev also expressed concern over the situation in the Brcko area in Bosnia.
